        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I think that Zend_Controller_Router_Route::assemble() must use default values for all parameters if $reset = true. For now it doesn't use defaults.\nFor example, I have route:\n{code}$router->addRoute('releases', new Zend_Controller_Router_Route('press\/releases\/:id', \n    array('controller' => 'releases', 'action' => 'release', 'module' => 'default')));{code}\nand url\n{code}http:\/\/example.com\/press\/releases\/1{code}\nin some plugin for front controller I want to assemble default uri for route with name 'releases'. I'm doing like this\n{code}$route = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance()->getRouter()->getCurrentRoute();\n$path = $route->assemble(array(), true);{code}\nand recieve in path\n{code}press\/releases\/1{code}\nbut I want to recieve\n{code}press\/releases{code}\n\nThat is a quick fix:\n{code}-                } elseif (isset($this->_values[$part['name']])) {\n+                } elseif (! $reset && isset($this->_values[$part['name']])) {{code}"
        },
